    explanation: 'The argument equates "many engineers" and "long development time" with reliability. However, a large team working for a long time does not guarantee a quality product — the work could be inefficient, poorly coordinated, or fundamentally misguided. This is a false equation of input quantity with output quality.\n\nWhy the other choices are wrong: A (emotional appeal) — there is no emotional language. C (circular reasoning) — the conclusion is not restating the premise. D (anecdotal evidence) — there is no evidence cited at all, let alone anecdotal. E (ad hominem) — no personal attack is made. The flaw is specifically the assumption that more effort necessarily means better quality.',
    tags: ['critical reasoning', 'flaw', 'logical fallacy'],
